.TH MD2ANSI 1 "2026-05-29" "md2ansi 1.0.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
md2ansi \- convert Markdown to ANSI-colored terminal output
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B md2ansi
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIFILE\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B md2ansi
is a zero-dependency C11 implementation that converts Markdown documents to
ANSI-colored terminal output. It reads Markdown from files or standard input
and produces richly formatted output suitable for terminal viewing.
.PP
The binary links only against the C standard library (no ncurses, no
terminfo, no regex). Scanners are hand-rolled, eliminating ReDoS attack
surface and giving predictable linear-time performance.
.PP
The tool supports a comprehensive set of Markdown features including
headers, lists, tables, code blocks with syntax highlighting, blockquotes,
inline and reference links, autolinks, inline formatting, task lists,
footnotes, backslash escapes, and YAML frontmatter stripping. All features
can be selectively disabled via command-line options.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Basic Options"
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display usage information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with detailed trace output sent to stderr. Each message
carries a timestamped sequence number so trace order is unambiguous when
piped.
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-width " \fIWIDTH\fR"
Force a specific terminal width instead of auto-detecting. Valid range is
20\-500 columns. Useful for generating output for specific display widths or
when terminal detection fails.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-plain
Enable plain text mode, disabling all feature toggles. Output is rendered
without rich formatting cues. Combine with
.B \-\-color=never
for pure plain text.
.TP
.BI \-\-color= MODE
Control ANSI colour output:
.B auto
(default, honours
.BR NO_COLOR " and " isatty (3)),
.BR always ", or " never .
.SS "Feature Toggle Options"
All Markdown features are enabled by default. Use these options to disable
specific features:
.TP
.B \-\-no\-footnotes
Disable footnote processing. Footnote references and definitions render as
plain text and no footnote section is emitted.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-syntax\-highlight
Disable syntax highlighting in fenced code blocks. Code displays in
monochrome without language-specific colouring.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-tables
Disable table formatting. Tables render as plain text without borders or
column alignment.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-task\-lists
Disable task list (checkbox) formatting. Task items render as regular list
items without checkboxes.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-images
Disable image placeholders. Image markup renders as plain text instead of
[IMG: alt] placeholders.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-links
Disable link formatting. Links render as plain text without underlining or
special formatting.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-bare\-urls
Disable autolinking of bare http(s):// URLs in text. Angle autolinks and
explicit `[text](url)` still render normally.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-table\-wrap
Disable wrapping of overlong table cells. By default, when a table's natural
width exceeds the terminal width, wide columns are word-wrapped so the table
fits; with this option the table is laid out at its natural width and may
overflow the right margin (matching the Bash implementation).
.SS "Other Options"
.TP
.B \-\-
End of options. All subsequent arguments are treated as filenames, even if
they begin with a dash.
.SH MARKDOWN FEATURES
.B md2ansi
supports a comprehensive set of Markdown elements:
.SS "Headers"
All heading levels H1 through H6 are supported with a distinct 256-colour
gradient:
.PP
.RS
H1 \- Bright yellow
.br
H2 \- Orange
.br
H3 \- Green
.br
H4 \- Blue
.br
H5 \- Purple
.br
H6 \- Dark gray
.RE
.PP
Inline formatting is supported within headers.
.SS "Inline Formatting"
.TP
.B Bold
Rendered using **text**
.TP
.I Italic
Rendered using *text* (neighbour-char guarded against snake_case clashes)
.TP
.BI "Bold Italic"
Rendered using ***text***, **_text_**, or _**text**_
.TP
.B Strikethrough
Rendered using ~~text~~
.TP
.B Inline Code
Rendered using `code`. Formatting inside backticks is suppressed (literal).
.TP
.B Inline Links
Rendered using [text](url) with underline and cyan colour.
.TP
.B Reference Links
Rendered using [text][ref] with [ref]: url definitions.
.TP
.B Shortcut Reference Links
Bare [ref] is matched against a definition if one exists.
.TP
.B Autolinks
Angle autolinks <https://...>, <mailto:...>, <ftp://...> render as cyan
underlined links. Bare http(s):// URLs in text are auto-linked by default
(disable with \-\-no\-bare\-urls).
.TP
.B Backslash Escapes
The 17 CommonMark backslash-escape characters are honoured: \\*, \\_, \\\\,
\\#, \\[, \\], \\(, \\), \\{, \\}, \\!, \\., \\+, \\-, \\>, \\~, and \\`.
.TP
.B Images
Rendered using ![alt](url) as [IMG: alt] placeholders.
.SS "Lists"
.TP
.B Unordered Lists
Using \- or * markers with proper indentation.
.TP
.B Ordered Lists
Using 1., 2., etc. with automatic numbering.
.TP
.B Task Lists
Using \- [ ] (unchecked) and \- [x] (checked) with checkbox symbols.
.TP
.B Nested Lists
Full support for nested lists (every 2 spaces of indent = one level), with
inline formatting inside list items and width-aware wrapping.
.SS "Tables"
GFM pipe-delimited tables with:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Column alignment: :--- (left), :---: (center), ---: (right)
.IP \(bu 2
Automatic column sizing via
.BR wcwidth (3)
(CJK characters count as 2 columns)
.IP \(bu 2
Unicode box-drawing borders (\(em \(br \(br etc.)
.IP \(bu 2
Inline formatting within cells (bold, italic, code, links)
.IP \(bu 2
Backslash-escaped pipes (\\|) preserved as literal content
.IP \(bu 2
Backtick-wrapped pipes (`a|b`) preserved as literal content
.IP \(bu 2
Overlong cells word-wrapped to fit the terminal width (disable with
.BR \-\-no\-table\-wrap ).
A single token wider than its column budget still overflows that column.
.RE
.SS "Code Blocks"
.TP
.B Fenced
``` or ~~~ delimited, with language specification on the opening fence.
.TP
.B Indented
4-space or 1-tab prefixed lines are treated as code blocks.
.PP
Syntax highlighting covers Python, JavaScript, and Bash with language
aliases (py, js, sh, shell). Keyword, string, number, comment, and function
tokens are coloured. Python docstrings (''' and \(dq\(dq\(dq) render in green.
.SS "Additional Elements"
.TP
.B Blockquotes
Using > prefix with dark background highlighting.
.TP
.B Horizontal Rules
Using ---, ===, or ___ (three or more), rendered with Unicode \(em chars.
.TP
.B Footnotes
Using [^id] references and [^id]: definition syntax. A footnote section is
auto-rendered at end of document. Missing definitions are shown in italic.
.TP
.B YAML Frontmatter
A block between --- lines (terminated by --- or ...) at the start of a
document is silently stripped before rendering.
.TP
.B Shebang Stripping
A leading #! line on file ingest is dropped, so executable Markdown scripts
render cleanly.
.SH COLOR SCHEME
.B md2ansi
uses a 256-colour ANSI palette for optimal terminal readability:
.SS "Element Colors"
.RS
.IP "Regular text" 18
Light gray (ANSI 38;5;7)
.IP "Code blocks" 18
Dark gray (ANSI 90)
.IP "Lists" 18
Cyan (ANSI 36)
.IP "Links" 18
Cyan-blue (ANSI 38;5;45) with underline
.IP "Blockquotes" 18
Dark background (ANSI 48;5;236)
.IP "Horizontal rules" 18
Cyan (ANSI 36)
.IP "Tables (chrome)" 18
Dark gray (ANSI 38;5;238)
.RE
.SS "Syntax Highlighting Colors"
.RS
.IP "Keywords" 18
Pink/Magenta (ANSI 38;5;204)
.IP "Strings" 18
Green (ANSI 38;5;114)
.IP "Numbers" 18
Yellow (ANSI 38;5;220)
.IP "Comments" 18
Dark gray (ANSI 38;5;245)
.IP "Functions" 18
Cyan (ANSI 38;5;81)
.IP "Classes" 18
Orange (ANSI 38;5;214)
.IP "Built-ins" 18
Light purple (ANSI 38;5;147)
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS "Basic Usage"
View a Markdown file with ANSI colors:
.PP
.RS
.nf
md2ansi README.md
.fi
.RE
.SS "With Pagination"
.PP
.RS
.nf
md2ansi README.md | less \-R
.fi
.RE
.SS "From Standard Input"
Process Markdown from a pipe or heredoc:
.PP
.RS
.nf
echo "# Hello **World**" | md2ansi
cat document.md | md2ansi
.fi
.RE
.SS "Multiple Files"
.PP
.RS
.nf
md2ansi file1.md file2.md file3.md
.fi
.RE
.SS "Custom Terminal Width"
.PP
.RS
.nf
md2ansi \-\-width 100 README.md
.fi
.RE
.SS "Force Colour Mode"
.PP
.RS
.nf
md2ansi \-\-color=always README.md > out.txt
md2ansi \-\-color=never  README.md > plain.txt
.fi
.RE
.SS "Debug Mode"
.PP
.RS
.nf
md2ansi \-\-debug README.md 2>debug.log
.fi
.RE
.SS "Disable Specific Features"
.PP
.RS
.nf
md2ansi \-\-no\-tables \-\-no\-syntax\-highlight README.md
.fi
.RE
.SS "Plain Text Mode"
.PP
.RS
.nf
md2ansi \-\-plain \-\-color=never README.md > output.txt
.fi
.RE
.SS "Pipelines"
.PP
.RS
.nf
git log \-\-format=%B | md2ansi
.fi
.RE
.SH SECURITY
.B md2ansi
includes several defences to handle untrusted input safely:
.SS "File Size Limits"
Maximum file size is 10MB (defined by
.B MD_MAX_FILE_SIZE
in
.IR md_common.h ).
Files larger than this are rejected with exit code 9. The stdin path has
the same cap with fail-fast behaviour.
.SS "No Regex Engine"
All scanners are hand-rolled. There is no
.BR regex (3)
library use anywhere in the binary, eliminating ReDoS attack surface and
giving deterministic linear-time scanning behaviour.
.SS "Input Sanitization"
All input is sanitised on ingest to remove ANSI escape sequences (CSI / OSC
/ SGR), preventing terminal-injection attacks via crafted Markdown.
.SS "Bounds Checking"
Terminal width is clamped to [20, 500]; invalid values cause exit 22.
Directories supplied where a file is expected are rejected with exit 4.
Unreadable files return exit 13 with a clear error message.
.SS "No Shell-Out"
The binary makes no
.BR system (3)
calls, runs no subprocesses, creates no temporary files, and never invokes
a shell. The entire pipeline is in-memory.
.SH PERFORMANCE
.B md2ansi
is optimised for low-latency terminal viewing:
.PP
.RS
Startup:     <1ms (single libc relocation + palette setup)
.br
Throughput:  ~5MB/sec on a typical desktop CPU
.br
Memory:      O(file size); a 10MB input peaks at ~25\(en30MB RSS
.br
File limit:  10MB
.br
Binary size: ~54KB dynamically linked
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TERM
Terminal type. Used to detect dumb terminals (turns colour off in
.B \-\-color=auto
mode).
.TP
.B COLUMNS
Fallback terminal width if
.BR ioctl (TIOCGWINSZ)
fails. If both are unavailable, defaults to 80.
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
If set (to any value), disables colour output under
.B \-\-color=auto
mode. Honours the
.UR https://no\-color.org
NO_COLOR
.UE
convention. Overridden by an explicit
.B \-\-color=always
flag.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.B \-\-help
and
.B \-\-version
also exit 0.
.TP
.B 3
File not found.
.TP
.B 4
Path is a directory.
.TP
.B 8
Required option argument missing (e.g.
.B \-\-width
without a value).
.TP
.B 9
Input exceeds 10MB size limit.
.TP
.B 13
Cannot read file (permission denied).
.TP
.B 22
Invalid option or argument (EINVAL).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I md2ansi
The compiled C executable. Installs by default to
.I /usr/local/bin/md2ansi
(root) or
.I $HOME/.local/bin/md2ansi
(unprivileged user).
.TP
.I md2ansi.1
This manual page. Installs to
.I $(MANDIR)/md2ansi.1
(default
.IR /usr/local/share/man/man1/ ).
.TP
.I md
Bash pager wrapper. Delegates to
.B md2ansi
and pipes the output through
.BR less (1)
with
.B LESS=\-FXRS
so ANSI escapes survive and short documents auto\-exit.
.TP
.I mdview
Bash browser-based preview utility. Converts Markdown to themed HTML via
.BR pandoc (1)
and opens it in a browser window. Recursively converts linked .md files
with inter-file link rewriting via the bundled Lua filter
.IR rewrite-md-links.lua .
.TP
.I md-link-extract
Bash utility that extracts every URL from one or more markdown files.
Strips UTM tracking query parameters.
.TP
.I ansi-info
Bash utility that prints the 256-colour palette, SGR attributes, truecolor
ramps, and terminal capability info.
.TP
.I md2ansi.bash_completion
Bash completion for
.BR md2ansi ", " md ", " mdview ", " md-link-extract ", and " ansi-info .
Installs to
.I $(COMPDIR)
(default
.IR /usr/local/share/bash-completion/completions/md2ansi ).
.TP
.I mdview.conf
Default configuration for
.BR mdview .
Installs to
.IR $(DATADIR)/mdview.conf .
Sets default theme, window size, and browser preferences as
.B MDVIEW_*
variables.
.TP
.I themes/
Theme directory for
.BR mdview .
Each theme is a pair of files
.RI ( name .css " for page styling, " name .theme " for pandoc syntax")
under
.IR $(DATADIR)/themes/ .
Bundled themes:
.BR github-dark " (default), " github-light "."
.SH ENVIRONMENT (mdview)
.B mdview
honours the following variables in addition to the core
.B md2ansi
environment:
.TP
.B MDVIEW_THEME
Theme name (default:
.BR github-dark ).
Overridden by
.BR \-t / \-\-theme .
.TP
.B MDVIEW_WINDOW_SIZE
Browser window dimensions as WIDTHxHEIGHT (default: 960x1080). Overridden
by
.BR \-s / \-\-window-size .
.TP
.B MDVIEW_BROWSER
Browser executable path. If unset,
.B mdview
auto-detects:
.BR google\-chrome ", " chromium\-browser ", " chromium ", then " xdg\-open .
Overridden by
.BR \-b / \-\-browser .
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for user configuration files (default:
.IR ~/.config ).
.B mdview
reads
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/mdview/mdview.conf
if present.
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Base directory for user data files (default:
.IR ~/.local/share ).
.B mdview
searches
.I $XDG_DATA_HOME/mdview/themes/
for user-installed themes (these take precedence over the system theme
directory).
